    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-30T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-30T04:00:00-05:00" n="1597"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1597">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.918/7–3049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-30T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 30, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 31—2:21 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1661. Protest Gould–Miner case (Embtel 1660, July 30) received by third-ranking
                    official Aliens Affairs Office and taken to inner office <pb facs="1263"
                        n="1253" xml:id="pg_1253"/> where presumably read by his superiors. It then
                    returned to Embassy officer with statement could not be accepted because
                    Shanghai outside jurisdiction Nanking AAO.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated Shanghai 920.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
